{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G4 child-consistency — container review of parent 1f19-adf2-ffb2-4b09 paired with this child (S6 Docs)]\n\nRan the 7 cross-child interaction modes for this Docs child against the WHOLE sibling roster (S1 6d56, S2 70c7, S3 fa49, S4 30b3, S5 b7fa). All seven modes are clean under the high-confidence / benign-reading filter. EMPTY findings list for this pairing.\n\nMode-by-mode:\n\n1. Implicit shared state — CLEAN. Every value this child documents has a single, named producer: REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR + the disk-cap (S1 portability seam / S2 janitor), the descriptive credential error message+remedy (S1 AC5 raises it), ref/source + origin/main default (S3 threads, S5 surfaces), the in-toto Statement shape + HMAC limits (S4, which in its AC5 explicitly delegates the trust-model docs \"via S6\"). No shared-state value is documented without a producer; documented values are mutually consistent.\n\n2. Conflicting assumptions — CLEAN. Every doc claim matches the behavior it describes: attested = pinned SHA / signs / records verified_at_sha (S4 AC1, S3 AC1/AC5); local = in-place checkout / never signs (S3 AC2 marks-unsigned, S4 AC2 bars-signing); \"attested fails closed while local still runs\" (S1 AC5); origin/main default (S3/S5). No contradiction with any sibling.\n\n3. Dependency gap — CLEAN. This child is a pure documenter; each documented obligation is claimed by a named sibling (credential error S1; ref/source S3+S5; in-toto/HMAC S4; tmpdir/disk-cap S1/S2). Considered the S5-introduced REBAR_ROOT-semantics doc obligation (\"document that REBAR_ROOT only locates the object DB to fetch from\", S5 What bullet 3): that obligation is claimed by S5's OWN What, and S5 scopes \"prose docs (S6)\" out — a benign prose-vs-schema split, not a high-confidence unowned gap at this child. README already carries REBAR_ROOT in the MCP-setup block (README.md:193, :261) and jira-sync-setup.md (this child's file_impact targets) both exist, so the doc surfaces this child names are real.\n\n4. Scope overlap — CLEAN. ref/source semantics: this child owns the PROSE docs; S5 owns the schema-level documented defaults inline — each scoped out of the other (S5 Scope: \"Out: prose docs (S6)\"). in-toto Statement shape: S4 BUILDS the envelope, this child DOCUMENTS it (S4 AC5 names the S6 hand-off). Clean producer/documenter splits; no double-implementation.\n\n5. Ordering violation — CLEAN. All six children carry empty deps uniformly and parent AC8 only requires all-closed + green; no ordering contradiction is asserted anywhere. Docs-after-behavior is a soft sequencing, not an encoded gap (consistent with the posture accepted across the roster's prior G4/G3 reviews).\n\n6. Consumer impact — CLEAN. This child is a terminal consumer/documenter; it produces no API/schema/env surface that a sibling depends on, so it imposes no downstream breakage.\n\n7. Residual references — CLEAN. All cross-refs resolve: jira-sync-setup.md (exists), README.md (exists), REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR (S1), the EFS/NFS flock caveat xref alto-fruit-punch (matches the parent's Out-of-scope note), in-toto Statement (S4), and \"Out: code (S1-S5)\" (all five siblings present in the roster).\n\nNote (not a G4 finding here): the standing dependency-gap finding on sibling S4 (30b3) about routing the pinned-SHA snapshot handle into plan_review/attest.py is a seam between S3 and S4; it does not touch this Docs child and is out of this pairing's scope.\n\nConclusion: no high-confidence cross-child inconsistency between this Docs child and the parent/siblings. No G4 finding for this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782520565554456001,"uuid":"a2ca15ee-b901-4f3c-a5f5-aa4712d3bcee"}